				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Speedrone: Fly or Die" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Speedrone: Fly or Die is a board game about mad deadly races between high-tech drones in a near future (2050). The goal is to win the race with your drone collecting as many Acceleration cards you can.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this period the military technologies become common and spread among civil people. Children and adults from every class of the society begin to build their own fighting drones in order to run in clandestine and official races. To achieve victory they are ready to do everything legal and illegal: there was no chance for pity or alliances, but only for the dangerous gadgets that drones equip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Speedrone: Fly or Die! it's a modular game: with a box you can play up to 5 players, with two boxes up to 10 and with 3 boxes up to 15 and so on. It's very simple and you do not need any extra components: the manual included in Speedrone - fly or die! - already contains everything you need to know.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game-play is very simple: every player acts in a specific order that changes during the game, draws cards and plays every cards he/she wants. Acceleration cards drive you to the victory, other cards like Shellfire force you to lose positions; many cards protect drones from the deadly gadgets of the game and other cards called Event tell you in which situation you are in that round. There are a lot of cards and a high combination of strategies in Speedrone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
